  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>As a bonus action, you can manifest a spectral tail as a natural weapon and immediately attack with it. If you hit with the tail, you deal force damage equal to 1d6 + your Strength modifier or Dexterity modifier (You choose this when you manifest the tail), instead of the bludgeoning damage normal for an unarmed strike. Furthermore, if there are creatures within 5 feet of your initial target for your tail attack, you can deal force damage equal to the modifier you chose when attacking them.</p><p>You can use this bonus action a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest. Additional, you regain a use of this bonus action when you expend a Hit Die.</p>",
